Bridge Design Competition

The Delaware Bridge Design Competition is a hands-on engineering competition aimed to engage students interested in math, science, and engineering fields. The program is designed to encourage middle and high school students to address real-world problems and inspire them to consider careers in transportation and civil engineering. Find out More....

Strategic Highway Safety Plan (SHSP)

Strategic Highway Safety Plan (SHSP) is a Comprehensive transportation safety plan with a goal of reducing highway fatalities and serious injuries on all public roads. To learn more, visit DSHP website.

    Highways, Bike Paths and DART Adopt a Shelter programs helps significantly reduce the roadside trash problem. This improves the look of IDelaware communities.

    View More

    Integrated Transportation Management System (ITMS) is DelDOT's way of integrating technology, infrastructure and people to achieve mobility, safety and security goals.

    View More

    The DelDOT Dashboard is a tool that provides information and analysis on performance measures for roads, bridges and services maintained by the state.
